646
00:41:03,950 --> 00:41:05,950
The patient wanted a heart transplant,

647
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:07,600
but couldn't find a suitable donor.

648
00:41:08,270 --> 00:41:09,120
And after much deliberation,

649
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:11,080
they did a partial left ventriculostomy.

650
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:12,720
The Batista surgery?

651
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:14,640
Yes.

652
00:41:15,430 --> 00:41:16,680
The surgery lasted exactly 11 hours.

653
00:41:17,080 --> 00:41:18,680
Professor Wu initiated the surgery,

654
00:41:18,950 --> 00:41:20,240
and Su Yun took over

655
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:21,910
after Professor Wu
showed signs of fatigue.

656
00:41:23,040 --> 00:41:25,040
He removed 302 grams of cardiac muscles.

657
00:41:26,750 --> 00:41:28,120
The operation was a success,

658
00:41:29,640 --> 00:41:31,160
but the patient
remained in critical condition.

659
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,720
The death rate of the Batista surgery

660
00:41:32,870 --> 00:41:34,000
is as high as 20%.

661
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:36,910
You know of it,

662
00:41:38,270 --> 00:41:39,640
